<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5747/22.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Panama</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Panama</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-27"><hi rend="italic">May 27,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform your
                            excellency that by a cable I have received to-day from my Government I
                            am instructed to advise your excellency that His Excellency Dr. M.
                            Amador Guerrero, President of Panama, has appointed Señors Gil Ponce
                            Jaen and Santiago de la Guardia to discharge the duties stipulated in
                            Article VI of the convention of November 18, 1903.</p>
                        <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. J. Arosemena.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>